}

.walkme-custom-balloon-content{
	font-family: "Cambria","Georgia",serif !important;
	color: #000 !important;
	font-size: 15px !important;
	line-height: 1.4em !important;
	padding: 18px 16px 16px 16px !important;

.walkme-custom-no-buttons .walkme-custom-balloon-title{
	border-bottom: none !important;
}
.walkme-custom-no-buttons .walkme-custom-balloon-buttons-wrapper{
	height: auto !important;
}

.walkme-custom-side-border,
.walkme-custom-balloon-separator{
	display: none !important;
}

.walkme-custom-balloon-buttons-wrapper{
	text-align: center !important;
	height: 43px !important;
}

}

						<p>Price improvement details provided for domestic stock and single leg option orders entered during market hours after the primary opening, provided there is a National Best Bid and Offer (NBBO) at the time the order is placed. 						<p>Buy market orders with a weighted average <a href="javascript:popLargerWin('https://scs.fidelity.com/webxpress/help/topics/help_definition_e.shtml#executionprice')">execution price</a> below the National Best Offer (NBO) are considered price improved. Price improvement for buy market orders is calculated by subtracting the weighted average execution price from the NBO, then multiplying by the number of executed shares to arrive at the net price improvement for the order. Price improvement on buy limit orders is calculated as the lesser of the NBO minus the execution price and the limit price minus the execution price. Sell market orders with a weighted average execution price above the National Best Bid (NBB) are considered price improved. Price improvement for sell market orders is calculated by subtracting the NBB from the weighted average execution price, then multiplying by the number of executed shares to arrive at the net price improvement for the order. Price improvement on sell limit orders is calculated as the lesser of the execution price minus the NBB and the execution price minus the limit price.</p>

						<p>Total Price Improvement reflects the sum of net price improvements on eligible orders executed within the stated timeframe. Orders with a weighted average execution price above the ask (for buys) or below the bid (for sells) are not factored into the Total Price Improvement figures.
